{
  "stem": "7739.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If anybody can see a civilian population being forced out of their houses.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They weren't able to take any possessions that was dear to them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You have people-- old people who cannot walk, or crippled people who aren't as fast to obey the commands from the soldiers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I still get nightmares from it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Although the Jewish population before the war was about 3,000, at the day of the expulsion, I would imagine it must have been at least between 8,000 and 10,000 people, because not only the two trainloads of people who came from Lodz and Plotzk, the people from the adjoining villages were expelled well prior to that, and they also came to live in the-- in the town of Wierzbnik.",
      "word_count": 73
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] At the day of the expulsion, we went out, because we lived only two houses away from the market square, so it wasn't far to go.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was on the way to work already in the morning, and I could see a lot of strange soldiers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You get to know the occupation soldiers-- you know, you got to know the gendarmes, and the Ukrainians who were the guards at the factory.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You get to see different uniforms, different soldiers, rounding up the people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I went back instead of going to work, and I alarmed, like, my family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we were prepared more or less for it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had a special suit made from strong material, which should last long.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I put on two or three shirts, in case my rucksack would be taken away, so at least I would be warm.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we marched out to this expulsion, besides seeing all the brutalities on the way.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Many people were shot, many people were beaten up.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
